ResponseBody:
WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
Skills and abilities. Batman has no inherent superpowers. He relies on his own scientific

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:13.000
knowledge, detective skills, and athletic prowess. In the stories, Batman is regarded

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:18.000
as one of the world's greatest detectives, if not the world's greatest crime solver.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:23.000
Batman has been repeatedly described as having genius-level intellect, one of the greatest

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:30.000
martial artists in the DC universe, and having peak human physical conditioning. He has traveled

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:36.000
the world acquiring the skills needed to aid his crusade against crime. His knowledge and

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:41.000
expertise in almost every discipline known to man is nearly unparalleled by any other

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:49.000
character in the universe. Batman's inexhaustible wealth allows him to access advanced technology.

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:55.000
As a proficient scientist, he is able to use and modify those technologies to his advantage.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:03.000
Batman describes Superman as the most dangerous man on earth, able to defeat a team of superpowered

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:12.000
extraterrestrials by himself in order to rescue his imprisoned teammates in the first storyline.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:18.000
Superman also considers Batman to be one of the most brilliant minds on the planet.

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:25.000
Batman has the ability to function under great physical pain and withstand mind control.

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:32.000
He is a master of disguise, multilingual, and an expert in espionage, often gathering

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:41.000
information under different identities. Batman's karate, judo, and jujitsu training has made

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:51.000
him a master of stealth and escape, allowing him to appear and disappear at will, and to break free
